.TH SIMPLE-SHELL 1 "December 22, 2023" "0.1" "Simple Shell User Manual"

.SH NAME

Simple Shell

.SH SYNOPSIS:

Simple Shell \- A simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH DESCRIPTION:

Simple Shell is a simple UNIX command interpreter designed for Holberton School. It supports interactive command entry, executiom of shell commands, and basic environment variable handling.

.SH OPTIONS:
.TP
.B -h, --help - Display help message and exit.

.SH COMMANDS:
.TP
.IP \(bu 2
.B trim_whitespace(str) -
Remove leading and trailing whitespaces from a string.

.IP \(bu 3
.B get_command(command, interactive) -
Read user input for the command.

.IP \(bu 4
.B execute_command(full_command, last_status) -
Execute a shell command.

.SH INTERACTIVE MODE:

	When run interactively, Simple shell displays a prompt ($) and waits for user input.
 Commands are executed as entered.

.SH NON-INTERACTIVE MODE:

	Simple shell can also be used in non-interactive mode by piping commands.
.TP
For example: echo /bin/ls | ./simpleshell

.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLE:
.TP
\fBPATH\fP -
A colon-separated list of directories where the shell looks for executable files.

.SH Return Value
The Simple Shell Program returns the exit status of the last command execute.

.SH EXAMPLES:

.IP \(bu 2
Run the shell interactively: ./simpleshell

.IP \(bu 3
Run a command non-interactively: echo /bin/ls | ./simpleshell

.SH SEE ALSO

.TP
